      <groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state>
      <groundspeak:short_description html="True">&lt;b&gt;31 March 2026, 07:00 - 07:30&lt;/b&gt;</groundspeak:short_description>
      <groundspeak:long_description html="True">&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;I plan on being in the area finishing up the geo-tour and working my way back towards Omaha today and figure I better start off with a hearty breakfast!  The only thing that makes a hearty breakfast better is when I can spend it with other cachers!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style="font-size:14px;"&gt;I will arrive early to get us a table.  My muggle hubby will be with me and I will be wearing a geocaching t-shirt.  I hope you stop by to say hello!  Note that even though the event is at a restaurant, no purchase is necessary to attend the event!&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description>
      <groundspeak:encoded_hints>McDonald's</groundspeak:encoded_hints>
      <groundspeak:logs>
        <groundspeak:log id="1352118595">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-03-31T14:16:28Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Attended</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="5549208">poeanne</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Enjoyed a nice breakfast with my ride or die, well he did at least. I am still dumbfounded that no restaurant on this trip has Coke Zero so I passed on breakfast. It will be my last morning of convenient mart grub. See you next year Norfolk! </groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1352116275">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-03-31T14:00:30Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Announcement</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="5549208">poeanne</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">I am sitting right behind the kiosk with my hubby. Wearing a red Georgia Bulldog shirt. </groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1348474669">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-03-11T04:10:07Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Publish Listing</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="531429">Heartland Cacher</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Published</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
        <groundspeak:log id="1351177830">
          <groundspeak:date>2026-03-25T19:00:00Z</groundspeak:date>
          <groundspeak:type>Will Attend</groundspeak:type>
          <groundspeak:finder id="3067478">JavaJudt</groundspeak:finder>
          <groundspeak:text encoded="False">Oh dang! I totally missed this publishing. It is a bit early for my normal schedule, but I'll try to make it.</groundspeak:text>
        </groundspeak:log>
      </groundspeak:logs>
    </groundspeak:cache>
  </wpt>
  <wpt lat="41.138317" lon="-96.040333">
    <time>2026-03-21T12:00:00</time>
    <name>GCBJ9ZH</name>
    <desc>2026 Nebraskache Election &amp; Membership Meeting by Nebraskache, Event Cache (1.0/1.0)</desc>
    <url>https://coord.info/GCBJ9ZH</url>
    <urlname>2026 Nebraskache Election &amp; Membership Meeting</urlname>
    <sym>Geocache Found</sym>
    <type>Geocache|Event Cache</type>
    <groundspeak:cache id="10293445" archived="False" available="True" xmlns:groundspeak="http://www.groundspeak.com/cache/1/0/1">
      <groundspeak:name>2026 Nebraskache Election &amp; Membership Meeting</groundspeak:name>
      <groundspeak:placed_by>Nebraskache</groundspeak:placed_by>
      <groundspeak:owner id="157466">Nebraskache</groundspeak:owner>
      <groundspeak:type>Event Cache</groundspeak:type>
      <groundspeak:container>Other</groundspeak:container>
      <groundspeak:attributes>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="24" inc="1">Wheelchair accessible</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="41" inc="1">Stroller accessible</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="1" inc="0">Dogs</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="30" inc="1">Picnic tables nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="28" inc="1">Public restrooms nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="59" inc="1">Food nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
        <groundspeak:attribute id="27" inc="1">Drinking water nearby</groundspeak:attribute>
      </groundspeak:attributes>
      <groundspeak:difficulty>1.0</groundspeak:difficulty>
      <groundspeak:terrain>1.0</groundspeak:terrain>
      <groundspeak:country>United States</groundspeak:country>
      <groundspeak:state>Nebraska</groundspeak:state>
      <groundspeak:short_description html="True">&lt;b&gt;21 March 2026, 12:00 - 15:00&lt;/b&gt;</groundspeak:short_description>
      <groundspeak:long_description html="True">&lt;h3&gt;&lt;big&gt;&lt;big&gt;2026 Nebraskache Election &amp;amp; Membership Meeting&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/big&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This event is from 12:00 - 3:00 PM on Saturday March 21st, and will take place at Ollie &amp;amp; Hobbes in Papillion. No purchase necessary to attend.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Ollie &amp;amp; Hobbes&lt;br /&gt;
310 E Gold Coast Rd&lt;br /&gt;
Papillion, NE&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(&lt;strong&gt;note location change&lt;/strong&gt; due to other place required purchase of buffet to  enter restaurant)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We&amp;#39;ve scheduled enough time to ensure there is time for folks to eat and visit, and subsequently hold the membership meeting - perhaps with some extra buffer time. Everybody is welcome to attend the Nebraskache membership meeting, even if you are not a member of Nebraskache.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;12:00 - Event starts. Grab your food and grab a seat!&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;1:00 - We will plan to start the membership meeting between 1:00-1:15.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Positions open for election are:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;President Elect&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Secretary/Treasurer&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Area 1 Representative&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Area 2 Representative&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Area 3 Representative&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Area 4 Representative&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Based on Nebraskache bylaws article VI - elections, in the event that only one nomination is received for an executive committee position, the position will not be voted upon, and the nominee will assume the duties in the next term.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nebraskache Business&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Election&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Election results&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Future of the group/Unfilled positions&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Ideas/feedback/suggestions from area geocachers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt;&lt;a href="http://nebraskache.com/"&gt;&lt;img height="112" src="https://img.geocaching.com/9102f957-c986-41b5-acdb-a076bd017129.jpg" width="224" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p style="text-align:center;"&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
</groundspeak:long_description>
